Explanation:
- The deleteCoverItem method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/pricetable/deletecover", method = RequestMethod.POST). There is no class-level @RequestMapping in this controller, so the method-level value is the full path.
- The method attribute explicitly sets the allowed HTTP method to RequestMethod.POST, so POST is acceptable.
- No other @RequestMapping (GET/PUT/DELETE/PATCH/OPTIONS/TRACE/HEAD) is declared for this endpoint in the provided code. Per the requirement to base acceptability on the code (not framework runtime behavior), only the explicitly declared POST method is considered acceptable. Therefore HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE, and PATCH are marked false.
